# Nimbusly — project rules (always apply)

Instructions live in **`.cursor/rules/`**. Read and follow them before coding.

## Required reading

| When | File |
|------|------|
| Any work in this repo | `.cursor/rules/project-fundamentals.instructions.md` |
| New module or non-trivial change | `.cursor/rules/new-module-or-change.instructions.md` |

## Non-negotiables (summary)

- **UI:** shadcn / existing `components/ui/` — do not reinvent primitives
- **State:** Zustand in `lib/stores/` for shared client state
- **Styles:** Tailwind + `cn()` + theme tokens; `rounded-none` brand style
- **Copy:** i18n via `useT()` / `getServerT()` — update `types.ts`, `pl.ts`, `en.ts` (PL + EN always)
- **Constants:** domain values in `lib/constants/` (`as const` + types) — no magic strings for modes, roles, tabs, langs
- **Data:** Server Actions + Supabase; migrations in `supabase/migrations/`
- **Tests:** add/update `lib/**/*.test.ts` and Cypress specs; run `npm test`
- **Safety:** validate on server, check existence/ownership, no SQL injection, no secrets in code
- **React state:** explicit `useState<Type>(...)` on every `useState` call

If instructions conflict with a one-off user message, follow the user — otherwise prefer `.cursor/rules/`.
